<subSubSection id="3DD26518AA69CA131AA6CF34FCFA64DB" pageId="45" pageNumber="1971" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="75773693AA69CA131AA6CF34FEBB6433" blockId="45.[160,1155,1598,1727]" box="[160,285,1598,1623]" pageId="45" pageNumber="1971">
<emphasis id="47BCEA81AA69CA131AA6CF34FEBB6433" bold="true" box="[160,285,1598,1623]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="1971">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA69CA131AA6CF68FCFA64DB" blockId="45.[160,1155,1598,1727]" pageId="45" pageNumber="1971">
The specific epithet ‘Marcapata’ corresponds to the Quechuan word, which means on the summit; and also to Marcapata Valley, located in the Andes in southern 
<collectingCountry id="0DDF7603AA69CA1319F9CF8FFB9364F9" box="[1023,1077,1669,1693]" name="Peru" pageId="45" pageNumber="1971">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="B70CF871AA69CA131E46CF8FFB2564F9" box="[1088,1155,1669,1693]" country="Peru" name="Cusco" pageId="45" pageNumber="1971">Cusco</collectingRegion>
Department, which belongs to the Vilcanota mountain chain.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3DD26518AA6ACA101AA6C984FC3463FE" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AA6C984FEB262C3" blockId="46.[160,1156,142,410]" box="[160,276,142,167]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
<emphasis id="47BCEA81AA6ACA101AA6C984FEB262C3" bold="true" box="[160,276,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AA6C9B8FC3463FE" blockId="46.[160,1156,142,410]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="B2C84D10AA6ACA101B25C9B8FE1F62AE" authority="Ferretti &amp; Cavallo &amp; Chaparro &amp; Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Seimon &amp; West, 2018" authorityName="Ferretti &amp; Cavallo &amp; Chaparro &amp; Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Seimon &amp; West" authorityYear="2018" box="[291,441,178,202]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcapata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="47BCEA81AA6ACA101B25C9B8FE1F62AE" box="[291,441,178,202]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">H. marcapata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="5C8F57FAAA6ACA101BC4C9B8FDBD62AE" box="[450,539,178,202]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differ from those of all other species of 
<taxonomicName id="B2C84D10AA6ACA1019ECC9B8FB2562AE" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[1002,1155,178,202]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="47BCEA81AA6ACA1019ECC9B8FB2562AE" box="[1002,1155,178,202]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Hapalotremus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the colour pattern, being entirely black with red setae on dorsal abdomen urticating patch (
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA101AF4C9FDFEFF636B" box="[242,345,247,271]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1268,1291]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-72@4.[163,1152,142,1237]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. (a–f) Hapalotremus spp. habitus. (a) Hapalotremus albipes, female. (b) Hapalotremus major, female. (c, d) Hapalotremus martinorum. (c) Male. (d) Female. (e) Hapalotremus chasqui sp. nov., juvenile. (f) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female. Photos: a: Mauricio Pacheco Suarez; b: Juan Chaparro; c, d: Patricio Cavallo; e: Laura Montes de Oca; f: Josh Richards." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747251" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747251/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Figure 1f</figureCitation>
). Additionally, females of 
<taxonomicName id="B2C84D10AA6ACA10188DC9FDFC85636B" authority="Ferretti &amp; Cavallo &amp; Chaparro &amp; Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Seimon &amp; West, 2018" authorityName="Ferretti &amp; Cavallo &amp; Chaparro &amp; Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Seimon &amp; West" authorityYear="2018" box="[651,803,247,271]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcapata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="47BCEA81AA6ACA10188DC9FDFC85636B" box="[651,803,247,271]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">H. marcapata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="5C8F57FAAA6ACA101928C9FDFC2E636B" box="[814,904,247,271]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from those of all other species by the femora of palp and legs I–IV bearing a single dorsal spine, in combination with the shape of the spermathecae having its basal portion much wider than apical; noticeably domed apical median region and apical lateral projections slightly developed (
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA101853C888FD6863FE" box="[597,718,386,410]" captionStart="Figure 29" captionStartId="33.[160,225,1162,1185]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-138@33.[163,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 29. (a–e) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female holotype (MUBI). (a) Labium, ventral view. (b) Eyes, dorsal view. (c) Tarsus IV, ventral view. (d) Tarsus IV, prolateral view. (e) Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747319/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Figure 29e</figureCitation>
). Male unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3DD26518AA6ACA101AA6C8D2FBA36422" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972" type="description">
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AA6C8D2FE806395" blockId="46.[160,1156,472,1606]" box="[160,294,472,497]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
<emphasis id="47BCEA81AA6ACA101AA6C8D2FE806395" bold="true" box="[160,294,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AA6C8F1FE4A603C" blockId="46.[160,1156,472,1606]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
<typeStatus id="AA738831AA6ACA101AA6C8F1FEA16077" box="[160,263,507,531]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Holotype</typeStatus>
female (MUBI): Total length (not including chelicerae and spinnerets) 40.0. Carapace: length, 17.3; width 15.2. Abdomen in bad condition: length 22.0. Fovea: slightly procurved, width 2.3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AC6CB69FC3860FA" blockId="46.[160,1156,472,1606]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
Colour pattern (live specimen): entirely black with pink hairs on margin of carapace and with red setae on dorsal abdomen urticating patch (
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA10192ACB8CFC3460FA" box="[812,914,646,670]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1268,1291]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-72@4.[163,1152,142,1237]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. (a–f) Hapalotremus spp. habitus. (a) Hapalotremus albipes, female. (b) Hapalotremus major, female. (c, d) Hapalotremus martinorum. (c) Male. (d) Female. (e) Hapalotremus chasqui sp. nov., juvenile. (f) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female. Photos: a: Mauricio Pacheco Suarez; b: Juan Chaparro; c, d: Patricio Cavallo; e: Laura Montes de Oca; f: Josh Richards." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747251" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747251/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Figure 1f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AC6CBA2FE2761D7" blockId="46.[160,1156,472,1606]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
Eyes: anterior eye row procurved, posterior recurved (
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA10191FCBA2FC3C60A4" box="[793,922,680,704]" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="32.[160,225,1206,1229]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1175]" captionTargetId="figure-141@32.[163,1152,142,1175]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figure 28. (a–d) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female holotype (MUBI). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Sternum, ventral view. (c) Abdomen, dorsal view. (d) Abdomen, ventral view. Scale bar: 5 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747317/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Figures 28a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA1019A0CBA2FC7760A4" box="[934,977,680,704]" captionStart="Figure 29" captionStartId="33.[160,225,1162,1185]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-138@33.[163,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 29. (a–e) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female holotype (MUBI). (a) Labium, ventral view. (b) Eyes, dorsal view. (c) Tarsus IV, ventral view. (d) Tarsus IV, prolateral view. (e) Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747319/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">29b</figureCitation>
). Eyes sizes and interdistances: AME 0.26, ALE 0.28, PME 0.30, PLE 0.19, AME–AME 0.38, AME–ALE 0.29, PME–PME 0.87, PME–PLE 0.16, ALE–PLE 0.24, Ocular tubercle: length, 1.4; width, 1.9. Clypeus: length, 0.3. Labium: length, 2.0; width, 2.6, with 18 cuspules (
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA1019FFCA1AFBD0614C" box="[1017,1142,784,808]" captionStart="Figure 29" captionStartId="33.[160,225,1162,1185]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-138@33.[163,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 29. (a–e) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female holotype (MUBI). (a) Labium, ventral view. (b) Eyes, dorsal view. (c) Tarsus IV, ventral view. (d) Tarsus IV, prolateral view. (e) Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747319/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Figure 29a</figureCitation>
). Maxillae: right with 126 cuspules, left with 112 cuspules. Sternum: length, 7.6; width, 7.2. Three pairs of sternal elongated sigillae, all pairs hardly visible (
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA1019F3CA5CFBD0610A" box="[1013,1142,854,878]" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="32.[160,225,1206,1229]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1175]" captionTargetId="figure-141@32.[163,1152,142,1175]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figure 28. (a–d) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female holotype (MUBI). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Sternum, ventral view. (c) Abdomen, dorsal view. (d) Abdomen, ventral view. Scale bar: 5 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747317/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Figure 28b</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae: with 13 well-developed teeth on promargin of furrow and 18 small teeth on the retromargin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AC6CAB4FDEC6604" blockId="46.[160,1156,472,1606]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Leg formula: IV&gt; I&gt; II&gt; III. Length of legs and palpal segments (femur, patella, tibia, metatarsus, tarsus, total): I: 11.9, 7.5, 8.4, 7.3, 5.0, 40.1; II: 11.6, 6.2, 5.8, 8.3, 5.1, 37; III: 10.1, 5.6, 6.5, 8.8, 5.4, 36.4; IV: 12.7, 6.5, 10.1, 13.5, 7.0, 49.8; palp: 7.7, 4.9, 6.0, –, 6.2, 24.8. Field of spiniform setae on basal retrolateral face of palp and legs I–IV. Spinnerets: PMS, 1.1 long; PLS, three-segmented, 5.8 long.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AC6CD61FE436754" blockId="46.[160,1156,472,1606]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
Scopulae: All tarsi densely scopulate and divided by conical long setae increasing in number from tarsus I to IV (
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA101BEDCD84FD2566C2" box="[491,643,1166,1190]" captionStart="Figure 29" captionStartId="33.[160,225,1162,1185]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-138@33.[163,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 29. (a–e) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female holotype (MUBI). (a) Labium, ventral view. (b) Eyes, dorsal view. (c) Tarsus IV, ventral view. (d) Tarsus IV, prolateral view. (e) Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747319/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Figure 29c, d</figureCitation>
). Metatarsi I 2/3 scopulate divided by three rows of setae, II 1/2 scopulate divided by three rows of setae, III 1/4 scopulate divided by approximately six rows of setae, IV with no scopulae. Dorsal face of all tarsi with two parallel rows of non-plumose clavate trichobothria interspersed with filiform, separated by a row of long, thin setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AC6CC31FEF567DF" blockId="46.[160,1156,472,1606]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
Chaetotaxy (left side): Femora of palp and Legs I–IV, 1d. Patellae of palp and Legs I–IV, 0. Tibiae: palp 2v, 1p; I 1p; II 1-1v, 1-1p, III 1-1-2v, 1-2-1p, 1-1r; IV 1-1-2v, 1-1-2-1p, 1-2-2- 1r. Metatarsi: I 1-2v; II 1-2v, 1p; III 2-2-1v, 1-1-2-2p, 2-2-2r; IV 1-1-2v, 2-2-1-2-2r, 2-1-1-1-2- 
<specimenCount id="63CEFD1AAA6ACA101AA6CCA9FF6567DF" box="[160,195,1443,1467]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972" type="generic">2p.</specimenCount>
Tarsi: I–IV 0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AC6CCCCFE8B6447" blockId="46.[160,1156,472,1606]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
Genitalia: Single spermathecal receptacle with basal portion much wider than apical; noticeably domed apical median region and apical lateral projections slightly developed (
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA101AAECF01FE866447" box="[168,288,1547,1571]" captionStart="Figure 29" captionStartId="33.[160,225,1162,1185]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-138@33.[163,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 29. (a–e) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female holotype (MUBI). (a) Labium, ventral view. (b) Eyes, dorsal view. (c) Tarsus IV, ventral view. (d) Tarsus IV, prolateral view. (e) Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747319/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Figure 29e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AC6CF24FBA36422" blockId="46.[160,1156,472,1606]" box="[192,1029,1582,1606]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
Urticating setae: 
<typeStatus id="AA738831AA6ACA101B87CF24FE116422" box="[385,439,1582,1606]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Type</typeStatus>
III present, abdomen in bad condition (
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA101987CF24FC5E6422" box="[897,1016,1582,1606]" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="32.[160,225,1206,1229]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1175]" captionTargetId="figure-141@32.[163,1152,142,1175]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figure 28. (a–d) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female holotype (MUBI). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Sternum, ventral view. (c) Abdomen, dorsal view. (d) Abdomen, ventral view. Scale bar: 5 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747317/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Figure 28c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3DD26518AA6ACA101AA6CF8EFC1564DB" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AA6CF8EFE6564F9" blockId="46.[160,947,1668,1727]" box="[160,451,1668,1693]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
<emphasis id="47BCEA81AA6ACA101AA6CF8EFE6564F9" bold="true" box="[160,451,1668,1693]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75773693AA6ACA101AA6CFADFC1564DB" blockId="46.[160,947,1668,1727]" box="[160,947,1703,1727]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">
Known only from the 
<typeStatus id="AA738831AA6ACA101B9ACFADFE6864DB" box="[412,462,1703,1727]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">type</typeStatus>
locality, at about 
<quantity id="B2309B76AA6ACA101898CFADFD5264DB" box="[670,756,1703,1727]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972" unit="m" value="3300.0">3300 m</quantity>
a.s.l. (
<figureCitation id="EDF32A16AA6ACA10193ACFADFC0064DB" box="[828,934,1703,1727]" captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="41.[160,225,846,869]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,815]" captionTargetId="figure-275@41.[163,1152,142,815]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 37. Distribution map of Hapalotremus species from Peru." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747338" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747338/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="1972">Figure 37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
